Grain salads are all the rage right now on social media, and beyond. But many of
them look more aspirational than inspirational—too fussy to put together on your
own. This one, however, is super simple while still being sophisticated enough
to show off to your followers. Just boil the farro, pop the veggies in the
oven, plate them with some greens and cheese, and voila! Insta-grain perfection.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil.
Add @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1} and @Farro{3/4%cup}. Cook until grains are
tender, ~{30-35%minutes}. Drain and return to #pot.

Wash and dry all produce. Halve and peel @Red Onion{1}(halved and peeled), then
cut into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss onion and @Butternut Squash{8%ounce}(cubed)
on a #baking sheet{} with @Olive Oil{} and season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.
Roast in oven until browned and tender, about ~{20%minutes}, tossing halfway
through.

Halve @Lemon{1}. Roughly chop @Almonds{1%ounce}.

Add onion, squash, almonds, @Dried Cranberries{1%ounce}, 1 1/2 TBSP olive oil,
and a squeeze of lemon to #pot with drained farro. Toss to combine. Season
with salt, pepper, and more lemon (to taste).

In a #medium bowl{}, toss @Arugula{2%ounce} with a squeeze of lemon and
@Olive Oil{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide salad between plates or wide bowls. Place farro mixture on top in a
mound. Using a #peeler{}, shave @Ricotta Salata Cheese{2%ounce}(shaved) over
plates, then serve.